Files:
- platform/mcp-server/src/loader.test.ts (remove duplicate test block)

Context:
After US-002, loader.test.ts no longer imports pluginNameFromPackage (it was moved to an @opentabs-dev/shared import for the tests). But the tests themselves are redundant — discovery.test.ts already tests pluginNameFromPackage with 9 comprehensive test cases that are a superset of the 4 in loader.test.ts.

Changes:

In platform/mcp-server/src/loader.test.ts, delete the entire describe('pluginNameFromPackage') block (lines 42-58):
```
describe('pluginNameFromPackage', () => {
  test('strips opentabs-plugin- prefix', () => {
    expect(pluginNameFromPackage('opentabs-plugin-slack')).toBe('slack');
  });

  test('handles third-party scoped packages', () => {
    expect(pluginNameFromPackage('@myorg/opentabs-plugin-jira')).toBe('myorg-jira');
  });

  test('strips official @opentabs-dev scope — treated like unscoped', () => {
    expect(pluginNameFromPackage('@opentabs-dev/opentabs-plugin-slack')).toBe('slack');
  });

  test('handles packages without the prefix', () => {
    expect(pluginNameFromPackage('some-other-package')).toBe('some-other-package');
  });
});
```

Also remove the `pluginNameFromPackage` import from @opentabs-dev/shared that was added in US-002 (since no code in the file uses it anymore after the test block is removed).

Constraints:
- Do NOT modify any other test blocks in loader.test.ts (validateTools, loadPlugin, checkSdkCompatibility, parseMajorMinor, etc.)
- Do NOT touch discovery.test.ts — it already has the comprehensive tests.
